# Workflow Rules

- At startup, each agent must discover the branch or worktree assigned to its role.
- Each agent must remember its assigned branch or worktree and work only there.
- The architect defines behavior and acceptance criteria, then notifies the coder.
- The coder implements one small slice at a time and notifies the reviewer.
- The reviewer runs deeper quality checks and notifies the coder and architect.
- The expected git layout must exist before work begins. Agents repair it or stop and report if it is missing.
- Agents must not silently work in the wrong branch or another role's worktree.
- Merge accepted changes only from the correct source branch for the role that produced them.
- Agents must use `swarmtools/notify-agent.sh` for handoffs.
- Every handoff must include the commit hash, branch name, what changed, and what was verified.
- Do not commit unrelated local changes or generated artifacts unless they are required for the slice.

## Context Hygiene

- Between sub-slices, send `/compact` to idle agents to summarize verbose intermediate tool-call and test-output noise while preserving constitution rules and reviewer carry-forwards.
- At major plan-phase boundaries, send `/clear` before the first slice of the next phase so the agent re-reads its role prompt and constitution fresh.
- Within a slice, send nothing. Mid-slice continuity matters; let the agent finish.
- If a `/compact` visibly drops important context, escalate to `/clear` on the affected agent.
